## DEC-031 — 2026-05-25 — Fix tx_sync_1 net merge failure (direct naming)

**Status:** APPLIED — ERC 13 confirmed 0 errors, 0 warnings. Netlist verified.

**Context:** DEC-030 added GLabels around pre-existing floating wires in adrv9009_signals.sch
to bridge FMC_H31_LA28_P ↔ HP_DP_38_P and FMC_H32_LA28_N ↔ HP_DP_38_N. Despite identical
format to all working signals, KiCad 5.1.5 did not merge the nets — the four pins still
appeared as isolated one-node stubs in the netlist (nets 237/238/254/255). ERC also reported
all four pins as unconnected (ErrType 2). Root cause: the tx_sync_1 wires in
adrv9009_signals.sch pre-existed from DEC-007 as purely decorative floating stubs with no
labels; adding GLabels around pre-existing floating wires in this context did not produce
net merging in KiCad's legacy resolver.

**Fix:** Bypass adrv9009_signals.sch routing entirely. Give both connector stubs the same
GLabel name directly in connectors.sch so they merge on the connectors sheet without
requiring a cross-sheet bridge.

