## 2026-04-27 — DEC-019 — DEF-11 power tree Architecture B adopted

**Status:** ACTIVE

**Decision:** Replace all single-stage LDOs in power.sch with Architecture B:
- B1–B4 (TPS54320, 3A sync buck) + L1–L4 (TPS7A85, 4A LDO) for MGTAVCC/MGTAVTT/VCCO_HP_65/VCCO_HP_64
- B5 (TPS54531, 5A buck, direct to 3.3V) for FMC_3P3V — no LDO
- FMC_3P3V excluded from two-stage: VITA57.1 only requires ±5%, no noise spec; LDO thermal at 5V→3.3V@3A would dissipate 5.1W (exceeds TPS7A85 Tj limit at defense ambient)

**Intermediate pre-reg voltages:**
- MGTAVCC 0.9V: 1.5V intermediate (VMGTAVCC_PRE)
- MGTAVTT 1.2V: 1.8V intermediate (VMGTAVTT_PRE)
- VCCO_HP_65 1.8V: 2.5V intermediate (VVCCO65_PRE)
- VCCO_HP_64 1.8V: 2.5V intermediate (VVCCO64_PRE)

**Sequencing:** SOM_PG_OUT → Buck EN → Buck PG → LDO EN (two-stage gating)

**Source:** TPS54320, TPS54531, TPS7A85, TPS7A84 datasheets; design-to-max from
Avnet UltraZed-EV Designer's Guide Table 33; VITA 57.1 FMC_3P3V noise requirement absent.

**Rationale:** TPS7A85 at 4A/4.4μVrms covers all four noise-sensitive rails with one
part number. TPS54320 at 3A with ≥33% headroom on all rails. Dropping LDO on FMC removes
thermal risk entirely while simplifying BOM.

