## 2026-04-14 — DEC-013 — Phase 5b pre-work: Q1-Q6 verified, DEF-11 opened, option γ approved

**Status:** VALID

**Context:** Beginning of Phase 5b (power.sch wire-up). Session-start diagnostic resolved DEC-012 (cosmetic connectors.sch re-save). Before writing any wires, the next step was answering six open design questions (Q1-Q6 from v4 transition doc Section 7.2) about LDO rail assignments, MGTVCCAUX topology, VADJ source, EN routing, GND topology, and PWR_FLAG policy. User provided three screenshots of power.sch showing the existing design notes and LDO blocks, which turned out to contain authoritative design intent for every question. User also uploaded three LDO datasheets (ADP7104.pdf, tlv1117.pdf, tps7a49.pdf) to project knowledge for primary-source verification of part claims from v2 memory.

**Q1-Q6 answers (verified from power.sch Design Notes block):**
- Q1a: U1=VCCO_HP_65 (1.8V), U2=VCCO_HP_64 (1.8V), U3=FMC_3P3V (3.3V), U4=MGTAVCC (0.9V), U5=MGTAVTT (1.2V). Matches v4 Section 4.5 inference exactly.
- Q1b: Declared parts per sheet annotations: U1/U2 = TLV1117-18 or AP2112K-1.8; U3 = TLV1117-33; U4/U5 = TPS7A4901 or ADP7104. Every declared part is inadequate — see DEF-11 below.
- Q2: MGTVCCAUX = direct short to VCCO_HP_65. No ferrite bead, no separate LDO. Decoupling via C15 4.7uF + C16 100nF. Design Note 4.
- Q3: VADJ = VCCO_HP_65, hardwired 1.8V fixed. VADJ and VCCO_HP_65 are the same net electrically. Design Note 3. VITA 57.1 Permission 5.12 allows this for closed systems.
- Q4: All five LDO EN pins tied to SOM_PG_OUT. Matches Avnet reference carrier (UGAESZU7EVSOMGV1_2 Figure 16). Design Note 1. DEF-2 (MGT rail sequencing) is RESOLVED by design — single SOM_PG_OUT gate handles all rails; no per-rail PGOOD daisy-chain needed.
- Q5: Single global GND net (power:GND). Matches SOM topology per Designer's Guide. No split planes.
- Q6: 6 PWR_FLAGs needed: VIN (barrel jack output), VCCO_HP_65 (U1 out), VCCO_HP_64 (U2 out), FMC_3P3V (U3 out), MGTAVCC (U4 out), MGTAVTT (U5 out). VADJ and MGTVCCAUX are shared with VCCO_HP_65 — no separate flags. Delete the 2 existing floating flags and place 6 new ones on actual wire endpoints.

**Primary-source datasheet verification (2026-04-14):**

ADP7104 Rev L (Feb 2026, analog.com) — VERIFIED:
- Title page: "20 V, 500 mA, Low Noise, CMOS LDO"
- Maximum output current: 500 mA (all package and voltage variants)
- Current limit foldback: typ 775 mA, max 1000 mA
- Packages: 8-lead LFCSP (3x3mm), 8-lead SOIC only. No 2A variant exists.
- Has EN/UVLO pin (pin 5), has PG pin (pin 7), has exposed pad
- Input range: 3.3V to 20V
- v2 memory claim "ADP7104ARDZ (2A)" is CONCLUSIVELY FALSE.

TLV1117 Rev O (June 2025, ti.com) — VERIFIED:
- Title: "15V, 800mA, Adjustable and Fixed Linear Voltage Regulator"
- Output current: 800 mA max
- Input voltage range: 2.7V to 15V recommended, 16V absolute max
- CRITICAL: cannot accept 12V input with any margin. A 12V nominal barrel jack that spikes to 15V+ exceeds absolute max.
- NO ENABLE PIN. 3-pin part (ADJ/GND, IN, OUT) plus NC in some packages. "Tie EN to SOM_PG_OUT" design intent is non-physical with this part.
- SOT-223 thermal: theta-JA = 95.4 degC/W. At 12V to 1.8V, 800mA dissipates 8.16W. Tj would exceed 800 degC. Realistic thermal-limited current in SOT-223 is ~100 mA at 12V to 1.8V.
- Dropout: 1.2V typ, 1.3V max at 800 mA (new chip). Massive dropout even at low currents.

TPS7A49 Rev E (May 2015, ti.com) — VERIFIED, and EARLIER CLAIM CORRECTED:
- Title: "36-V, 150-mA, Ultralow-Noise, Positive Linear Regulator"
- Output current: 150 mA max (NOT 1A as I stated earlier in this session, and NOT 1A as v2 memory claimed).
- Input range: 3V to 36V. Handles 12V easily.
- Adjustable ONLY: Vout range 1.194V to 33V. No fixed-voltage variants. Requires external resistor divider.
- HAS enable pin (pin 5), HAS NR/SS pin, HAS exposed pad
- HVSSOP PowerPAD (DGN) or VSON (DRB), both 3x3mm
- v2 memory claim "TPS7A4901 (1A) is insufficient" is WRONG twice over: (1) it is 150 mA, not 1 A, (2) the proposed "upgrade" ADP7104 at 500 mA is better but still nowhere near 1.8/2.0 A requirement.

**SOM current requirements (from UGAESZU7EVSOMGV1_2 Table 33):**
- VCCO_HP_64: 1.5 A
- VCCO_HP_65: 1.5 A
- MGTAVCC: 1.8 A
- MGTAVTT: 2.0 A
- MGTVCCAUX: 0.05 A
- FMC_3P3V: 3.0 A per VITA 57.1 Table 11 (for compatibility)

**Power dissipation math at 12V input (thermal reality check):**
- VCCO_HP_65 at 1.5A: (12-1.8)*1.5 = 15.3 W dissipation in the LDO
- VCCO_HP_64 at 1.5A: same 15.3 W
- FMC_3P3V at 3.0A: (12-3.3)*3.0 = 26.1 W
- MGTAVCC at 1.8A: (12-0.9)*1.8 = 20.0 W
- MGTAVTT at 2.0A: (12-1.2)*2.0 = 21.6 W
- Total worst-case LDO dissipation: ~98 W. Impossible in any standard IC package without heatsinking the size of a coffee mug. Board would need 100W+ of thermal dissipation as heat from linear regulation alone.

No linear regulator at any package size from any manufacturer can do this. The architecture — direct 12V to rail LDO — is fundamentally unsuitable regardless of part selection. This is a design-level defect, not a part-selection defect.

**DEF-11 — OPENED (HIGH PRIORITY, BLOCKS PCB LAYOUT):**
Power tree on power.sch is architecturally unsound. Phase 5c (new) must redesign before PCB fabrication. Candidate architectures:
(A) Two-stage: 12V buck to 5V intermediate then LDOs for all rails. Reduces LDO dissipation by ~60%.
(B) Three-stage with rail-specific intermediates: 12V buck to 5V then LDOs for VCCO/VADJ; 12V buck to 3.3V then LDO for FMC_3P3V; 12V buck to 1.8V then LDOs for MGTAVCC/MGTAVTT.
(C) All-switcher: 12V direct bucks for each rail using low-noise POL converters. Efficient but requires output filtering for RF-sensitive rails.
XPE (Xilinx Power Estimator) run is required to refine actual-load currents before part selection.

**Option gamma approved for Phase 5b:**
Proceed with Phase 5b wiring using the generic LDO_Fixed_EN library symbol. The symbol has pins IN/OUT/EN/GND which matches the topology that ANY properly-sized replacement part in Phase 5c will need: IN cap, OUT cap, EN tied to SOM_PG_OUT, GND. The wires being emitted in Phase 5b are independent of which specific part eventually populates the board. Phase 5b goal is ERC pass + electrically-correct generic topology. Phase 5c will replace the library symbol (or rebind footprint) when a real part is chosen.

Phase 5b scope is UNCHANGED by this decision: wire up 5 LDO blocks, barrel jack bulk decoupling, MGTVCCAUX share wire, VADJ share wire, GND ties, 6 PWR_FLAGs, delete 2 floating PWR_FLAGs. Target: 0 ErrType(3) on post-edit ERC.

