DEC-039 — Project end-use reclassified to commercial RF / SDR datalink
Date: 2026-06-09
Status: APPROVED

Previous framing of this project as defense-grade UAV/GCS datalink
(candidate for USML Cat XI Military Electronics and/or Cat VIII UAV)
is superseded. The project is reclassified as commercial RF / SDR
datalink carrier for UAV/GCS communications.

Engineering standards adopted under the prior framing are RETAINED
as voluntary engineering choices, positioned as product
differentiators rather than compliance requirements:
  - Power tree quality (DEC-036 US-supply-chain PD redesign,
    TPS25730D + TPS7A1633)
  - JESD204B PI / SI rigor
  - Conservative thermal and current margins
  - Defense-comparable part selection where adopted

Consequences:
  - T25 (ITAR determination) closes NOT-APPLICABLE.
  - Fab vendor selection no longer constrained by ITAR registration;
    MacroFab, Sierra, JLCPCB advanced, PCBWay advanced, etc. all
    candidates evaluated on IPC class, capability, cost, lead time.
